==============================================================================
Third-party code attribution
==============================================================================

This project incorporates code and architectural patterns from the following
projects. Each file containing lifted code carries an inline attribution
comment identifying the source commit.

----- Maestro -----
https://github.com/its-maestro-baby/maestro
MIT License, copyright (c) Maestro contributors.

The following modules are derived from Maestro:
  - src-tauri/src/core/process_manager.rs (PTY management)
  - src-tauri/src/core/terminal_backend.rs (backend trait abstraction)
  - src-tauri/src/core/session_manager.rs (session metadata)
  - src-tauri/src/core/utf8_decoder.rs (split-byte UTF-8 handling)
  - src-tauri/src/core/error.rs (PtyError types)
  - src-tauri/src/core/windows_process.rs (Windows ConPTY helpers)
  - src-tauri/src/commands/terminal.rs (Tauri command handlers)
  - src-tauri/src/commands/usage.rs (Anthropic OAuth usage API)
  - src/lib/pty.ts (frontend IPC wrappers; ports lib/terminal.ts)

The render-batching patterns and xterm.js wiring in the frontend
UI also derive from Maestro's src/components/terminal/TerminalView.tsx,
adapted from React to vanilla JS.

----- gmux-system (v3) -----
https://github.com/fivelidz/gmux-system
The v3 UI, voice daemon, gesture engine, agent monitor dashboard,
phone bridge protocol, memory aggregator, sub-agent system, and
provider auth panel are lifted from gmux-system v3.7.2. License terms
of the v3 repo apply to those derived components.

----- xterm.js, Tauri, portable-pty -----
All used per their respective licenses (MIT, MIT, MIT).
